2. EPFO Compliance Tycoon

Target stakeholders: Employers, HR managers, payroll staff, consultants
Game format: Business management simulation

The player runs a company with employees. Every month, they must complete EPFO-related responsibilities: employee registration, wage reporting, contribution deposit, ECR filing, KYC approval, exit date marking, nominee awareness, and compliance response.

Mistakes cause consequences like damages, interest, inspection alerts, employee grievances, and poor compliance rating.

Learning outcomes:

Employers learn due dates, wage components, contribution calculation, ECR filing, employee onboarding, exit management, and compliance risks.

Example challenges:

“You hired 25 employees. Are you covered under EPF Act?”
“One employee’s basic wage changed. Update contribution correctly.”
“You missed ECR filing deadline. What are the consequences?”
“Employee left last month. Mark exit date.”

Gamification:

Company compliance rating, “Zero Default Month” badge, digital compliance certificate, leaderboard among establishments.
